== Shareholder's Equity
\
1. Share Capital
  - Authorized $==>$ Maximum number of shares allowed to distribute
  - Issued $==>$ Number of shares sold to shareholders
  - Outstanding $==>$ Number of shares in shareholders hands (because company can purchase themselves' share, so shares in shareholders hands decreased)
2. Contributed Surplus
3. Accumulated other Comprehensive Income
4. Retained Earnings
\
== Classes of Shares
\
1. Common
 - Basic form of Capital
 - Has the Four Rights
 - Shareholders benefit if the company succeeds
2. Preferred
 - Has advantageover common 
   - Receive Dividends first
   - Receive Assets in first liquidation
 - Earn Fixed Dividends
 - Very Few corporation Issues

